- Yes, my dear.

154
00:14:17,880 --> 00:14:20,080
- A woman is asking for you.
- Who is she?

155
00:14:20,440 --> 00:14:21,960
She didn't say her name.

156
00:14:30,760 --> 00:14:33,760
- Hello.
- "Hello, Noura. How are you?"

157
00:14:33,880 --> 00:14:35,840
I'm good. Who is this?

158
00:14:35,960 --> 00:14:40,960
I'm Umm Murjana. You don't know me
but my daughter's wedding is tonight.

159
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:44,240
And she's insistent to have you
sing at her wedding.

160
00:14:44,360 --> 00:14:47,280
It's an honor, Umm Murjana,
but I'm afraid I can't tonight.

161
00:14:48,400 --> 00:14:50,200
It's the band's day off,
I won't be able to.

162
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:55,160
It's my fault, I should've called sooner
but I got too busy and forgot.

163
00:14:55,800 --> 00:15:00,080
If my daughter finds out I forgot
to call you, she'll be heartbroken.

164
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:03,840
I'm sorry, I can't.
My kids are home alone.

165
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:07,480
But I can give you the number
of another singer who can be there.

166
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:11,840
My daughter won't accept
anyone but you singing at her wedding.

167
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:14,520
I'll pay you double your fee, or more.

168
00:15:15,280 --> 00:15:18,400
Ask for whatever amount you want,
just come to the wedding.

169
00:15:27,800 --> 00:15:29,080
Okay.

170
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:38,400
Noura. Noura!

171
00:15:39,680 --> 00:15:41,560
- Say God's name.
- In God's name.

172
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:46,520
What's the matter? You look like
you're going to a funeral, not a wedding.

173
00:15:48,240 --> 00:15:51,760
I hate that my kids are home alone
on my day off.

174
00:15:51,920 --> 00:15:53,680
I thought you had something to do.

175
00:15:53,800 --> 00:15:57,840
But why else do we work this hard?
We do it for them, don't we?

176
00:15:58,000 --> 00:15:59,280
On another topic.

177
00:16:00,160 --> 00:16:05,720
How about tomorrow we take our kids
to the amusement park and have some fun?

178
00:16:07,520 --> 00:16:09,120
We always end up going on more rides
than they do.

179
00:16:09,240 --> 00:16:13,520
Why not? We're still young,
beautiful, and full of life.

180
00:16:13,640 --> 00:16:16,680
We didn't have stuff like that
back in the day.

181
00:16:16,880 --> 00:16:18,200
That's true.

182
00:16:19,400 --> 00:16:22,320
- Why is everyone so gloomy?
- May God protect us.

183
00:16:22,480 --> 00:16:27,560
Come on, guys. What's wrong with you?
We're going to a wedding, cheer up.

184
